"undergraduate research methods classes (DRIP and DRIP:A) in 2013. For you, "
"this book is ideal, because it was written to accompany your stats lectures. "
"If a problem arises due to a shortcoming of these notes, I can and will "
"adapt content on the fly to fix that problem. Effectively, you’ve got a "
"textbook written specifically for your classes, distributed for free "
"(electronic copy) or at near-cost prices (hard copy). Better yet, the notes "
"have been tested: Version 0.1 of these notes was used in the 2011 class, "
"Version 0.2 was used in the 2012 class, and now you’re looking at the new "
"and improved Version 0.3. I’[for a historical summary]m not saying these "
